Replay
 







 



 



 



 



 



 



 As more and more devices connect to the Internet – everything from trains to air conditioning units to smoke alarms – the potential for the Internet of Things (IoT) to drive efficiencies, increase productivity and promote economic growth is becoming reality. In particular, the IoT is fueling innovation and creating opportunities in the development of clean technology, and helping redefine what a sustainable world will look like. 
 Chris Buddin, Global Head of the Clean Technology and Renewables Group and Internet of Things at Goldman Sachs, explores the possibilities at the intersection of the IoT and clean technology.















 

Chris Buddin
Global Head, Clean Technology and Renewables Group and Internet of Things, Investment Banking Division, Goldman Sachs
Read Bio
 




The energy market is interesting because it’s so gigantic and the tech market is interesting because it’s dynamic, innovative and creates growth. So think of a future where we have IoT solutions deployed in the energy landscape… that’s a pretty exciting future.
 - Chris Buddin 







